        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 2:19PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 219 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of White Sands National Park, moving west at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
White Sands National Park, Northrup Landing, and Lake Lucero.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
